replies.bodyText:
freezeDirect() is OK.
But for attemptFreeze() if (by the slightest chance) there is an attempt to freeze the same value concurrently there is a chance it'll panic. https://github.com/ballerina-platform/ballerina-lang/blob/master/bvm/ballerina-runtime/src/main/java/org/ballerinalang/jvm/values/freeze/FreezeUtils.java#L45 unless we set the frozen flag when creating the value itself.
This IMO is unnecessary since it's making it read-only is always possible.
And for freeze() I think we can remove freezeDirect() call.
    @Override
    public Object freeze() {
        // freezeDirect(); we can remove this
        return this;
    }
